The idea of this list is that the people here should be the ones contacted if there are questions about the design of this file, I don't think this contribution is significant enough for that
Ah okay, no worries!
I think It's better to use `{f : ℕ →. ℕ // Nat.Partrec f}`

I think using the `choose` tactic gives a cleaner proof:
```suggestion
  choose v hv using fun x : {f : ℕ →. ℕ // Nat.Partrec f} ↦ Nat.Partrec.Code.exists_code.1 x.2
  suffices v.Injective from this.countable
  intro f g h
  ext
  simp [h, ← hv]
```
Thanks, `choose` seems useful.

```suggestion
/-- There are only countably many partial recursive partial functions `ℕ →. ℕ`. -/
instance : Countable {f : ℕ →. ℕ // _root_.Partrec f} := by
  apply Function.Surjective.countable (f := fun c => ⟨eval c, eval_part.comp (.const c) .id⟩) 
  intro ⟨f, hf⟩; simpa using exists_code.1 hf

/-- There are only countably many computable functions `ℕ → ℕ`. -/
instance : Countable {f : ℕ → ℕ // Computable f} :=
  @Function.Injective.countable {f : ℕ → ℕ // Computable f} {f : ℕ →. ℕ // _root_.Partrec f} _
    (fun f => ⟨f.val, f.2⟩)
    (fun _ _ h => Subtype.val_inj.1 (PFun.lift_injective (by simpa using h)))
```

I think the second proof would be clearer if it was in tactic mode. Something like this:
```lean 4
instance : Countable {f : ℕ → ℕ // Computable f} := by
  let g : {f : ℕ → ℕ // Computable f} → {f : ℕ →. ℕ // _root_.Partrec f} := fun f => ⟨f.1, f.2⟩
  refine Function.Injective.countable (f := g) fun _ _ h => Subtype.val_inj.1 (PFun.lift_injective ?_)
  simpa [g] using h
```
I'd probably split the `refine` block further, but I think that's up to taste.

I guess there are different philosophies --- (1) keep it succinct since mathematically it's not an interesting proof, or (2) make it easy to understand even if it's longer. Also what's clearer may depend on the reader and their taste/experience. :)

I do want to mention that having more readable proofs can still be useful for "trivial" results, especially if they have to be refactored later down the line. Bespoke term mode proofs have caused me trouble in the ordinal part of the library in the past...
Makes sense... well I'm fine with anything

```suggestion
    (fun _ _ h => Subtype.val_inj.1 (PFun.lift_injective (by simpa using h)))

```
